  <div>
      <p>
         <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_ablative_therapy">Ablative Therapy</xref>
 is a 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_clinical_intervention">CLINICAL INTERVENTION</xref>.         </p>
      <p>
         <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_ablative_therapy">Ablative Therapy</xref>
 (also called 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_ablative_therapy">Ablation Therapy</xref>) is the removal or destruction of a body part, 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_tissue">TISSUE</xref>
 or its function and may be performed by surgery, hormones, drugs, radiofrequency, heat, or other methods.        </p>
      <p>
For further information on 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_ablative_therapy">Ablative Therapy</xref>, see the 
              <xref href="https://www.cancer.gov/dictionary?CdrID=335061"
               scope="external"
               format="html">National Cancer Institute website</xref>.        </p>
  </div>
